article.headline: Lehigh 75, Army 64
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 30 points and Marquis Hall added 20, leading Lehigh to a 75-64 victory over Army on Saturday night. Olivero shot 6-for-11 from the field and 15-for-19 from the line for the Mountain Hawks (11-14, 6-4 Patriot League) Jarell Brown scored 23 points on 7-for-21 shooting, and Matt Bell added 11 points and six assists for Army (13-12, 3-7). Hall scored 12 first-half points and Olivero 10 as Lehigh took a 34-26 lead into the break. In the second half, Lehigh increased its lead to 10 points before Army cut its deficit to five. Lehigh pushed its lead to 12 points when Bryan White hit a jumper and Olivero added a 3-pointer to make it 55-43 with 12:21 left. Army rallied, closing within three points with 8:31 remaining, but Lehigh used a 6-0 run, capped by a 3-pointer by Olivero, to push its lead to nine and never looked back.
